title: Power Outages: An Investigative Analysis
description: Power outages are significant events, and can disrupt daily life, impact economic activities, and potentially pose risks to health and safety - especially ones on larger scales. We aim to answer the question of finding the characteristics of major power outages with high severity, and what risk factors an energy company might want to look into when predicting the location/severity of its next major power outage.

title: Neural Autoregressive flow for Data-driven background estimation
description: Developed a ML method to estimate major background shape and distribution in particle physics data. The project utilises a DNN finds transformation from input distribution (MC simulation) to target distribution (actual data). This has been presented at the ML forum at Fermi National Accelerator Laboratory and CERN as well as the APS April conference 2024
